"{\"uid\": \"mbr.co.uk-news-rubbings-racing-tom-pidcock-responds-to-boos-after-sharp-elbows-gold-medal-win-in-paris-2024-olympic-mountain-bike-xco-440299\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Pidcock becomes the second man ever to win two gold medals in mountain bike cross-country after controversial move and mid-race puncture.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Pidcock has won gold in the Olympic mountain bike XC, in one of the best comebacks of all time.Pidcock took the lead on the second lap, before a puncture saw him lose sightof Frenchman Viktor Koretsky in the lead, with 40 seconds separating him from gold at its biggest gap.\", \"from\": 139, \"to\": 417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 139, \"end\": 150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}, {\"begin\": 193, \"end\": 195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cross-country_cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.056526230059758e-38, \"text\": \"XC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cross-country_cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cross-country_cycling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It looked like game over for the reigning champion then, with Koretsky looking strong in the lead and on home turf in front of a French crowd.\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 548, \"end\": 554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5283335288426827, \"rank\": 0.571347178430999, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, Pidcock persevered and managed to not only reel in the race leader and the chasing group, but take the win in emphatic style.\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock's gold is the second for GB during theOlympicsso far, and is hissecond gold medal after he won in Tokyo- he has also become only the second man to win two golds in this discipline.\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 726, \"end\": 728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9918938569550865, \"rank\": 0.008172131775219443, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 799, \"end\": 804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999823729797914, \"rank\": 1.7557086617941747e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's Victor Koretzky (L) and Britain's Thomas Pidcock (R) compete in the men's cross-country mountain biking event during the Paris 2024 Olympic Games in Elancourt Hill venue in Elancourt, on July 29, 2024.\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 1093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 883, \"end\": 889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9927673758718502, \"rank\": 0.004530458483080368, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 892, \"end\": 907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\", \"score\": 0.9999880939516794, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Victor Koretzky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\"}, {\"begin\": 916, \"end\": 923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9266592590656564, \"rank\": 0.0788753783147212, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 926, \"end\": 940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}, {\"begin\": 1065, \"end\": 1074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"score\": 0.9725613440037943, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elancourt\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Photo by John MACDOUGALL / AFP) (Photo by JOHN MACDOUGALL/AFP via Getty Images)  What the course may havelacked in technicality,you can not deny that it kept the racing fast and close in the men's race.\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1161, \"end\": 1166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9999260910169231, \"rank\": 3.5833116638571516e-05, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The race was tight and attacks were short-lived until the 25 minute mark.\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Charlie Aldridge of GB marked the leaders well in the opening laps - and he managed to finish 8th in his first Olympics.\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1493, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1381, \"end\": 1389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\", \"score\": 0.9999983764441359, \"rank\": 9.69580076927817e-07, \"text\": \"Aldridge\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\"}, {\"begin\": 1393, \"end\": 1395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9918938569550865, \"rank\": 0.008172131775219443, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also won the unofficial award for the most steezy rider, after pulling t-bogs on one of the double jumps lap after lap.\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1616, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But after 25 minutes of racing Pidcock attacked uphill by the switchbacks, with only Viktor Koretsky of France able to follow.\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1722, \"end\": 1728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9927673758718502, \"rank\": 0.004530458483080368, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alan Hatherly of South Africa stayed close behind.\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1745, \"end\": 1758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\", \"score\": 0.9999924602050241, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alan Hatherly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\"}, {\"begin\": 1762, \"end\": 1774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.95811838541843, \"rank\": 0.02618891118019723, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two leaders worked well together, until Pidcock suffered a flat tyre.\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1870, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately he lost more time than necessary as the mechanics were not ready for him, and he ended up almost 40 seconds back from the leader Koretsky.\", \"from\": 1871, \"to\": 2023, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain's Thomas Pidcock cycles ahead of France's Victor Koretzky (L) and South Africa's Alan Hatherly (R) as they compete in the men's cross-country mountain biking event during the Paris 2024 Olympic Games in Elancourt Hill venue in Elancourt, on July 29, 2024.\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2025, \"end\": 2032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9266592590656564, \"rank\": 0.0788753783147212, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2035, \"end\": 2049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}, {\"begin\": 2066, \"end\": 2072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9927673758718502, \"rank\": 0.004530458483080368, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2075, \"end\": 2090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\", \"score\": 0.9999880939516794, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Victor Koretzky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\"}, {\"begin\": 2099, \"end\": 2111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.95811838541843, \"rank\": 0.02618891118019723, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 2114, \"end\": 2127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\", \"score\": 0.9999924602050241, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alan Hatherly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\"}, {\"begin\": 2260, \"end\": 2269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"score\": 0.9725613440037943, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elancourt\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Photo by Emmanuel DUNAND / AFP) (Photo by EMMANUEL DUNAND/AFP via Getty Images)  Of course, that did not deter the Leeds-born Pidcock, as he fought through the chasers and brought the gap back almost on his own.\", \"from\": 2289, \"to\": 2501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2299, \"end\": 2307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\", \"score\": 0.9990293733905197, \"rank\": 0.0009713306260288832, \"text\": \"Emmanuel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\"}, {\"begin\": 2317, \"end\": 2320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9999996725328483, \"rank\": 3.207416199099e-07, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}, {\"begin\": 2356, \"end\": 2361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9999260910169231, \"rank\": 3.5833116638571516e-05, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hatherly rode most of the race in no-man's land in between Koretsky and the chasers, until Pidcock reappeared and helped to bring back the Frenchman.\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the bell rung for the final lap, Pidcock led the group of Korestky and Hatherly towards the Wall climb.\", \"from\": 2652, \"to\": 2758, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you were eagle-eyed, you might have seen that Evie Richards came out to support Pidcock, cheering him on on the final lap up the early switchback climbs.\", \"from\": 2760, \"to\": 2916, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2809, \"end\": 2822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evie_Richards\", \"score\": 0.9999999329952538, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Evie Richards\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evie_Richards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evie_Richards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock attacked past the feed zone on the 50m climb into the woods, but it did not stick - Koretsky and Hatherly were stuck on his wheel.\", \"from\": 2917, \"to\": 3055, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"South Africa's Alan Hatherly competes in the men's cross-country mountain biking event during the Paris 2024 Olympic Games in Elancourt Hill venue in Elancourt, on July 29, 2024.\", \"from\": 3057, \"to\": 3235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3057, \"end\": 3069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.95811838541843, \"rank\": 0.02618891118019723, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 3072, \"end\": 3085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\", \"score\": 0.9999924602050241, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alan Hatherly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\"}, {\"begin\": 3207, \"end\": 3216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"score\": 0.9725613440037943, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elancourt\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Photo by Emmanuel DUNAND / AFP) (Photo by EMMANUEL DUNAND/AFP via Getty Images)  Koretsky looked calm and collected, attacking late on the last lap and managed to gap Pidcock going into the rock section.\", \"from\": 3236, \"to\": 3440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3246, \"end\": 3254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\", \"score\": 0.9990293733905197, \"rank\": 0.0009713306260288832, \"text\": \"Emmanuel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\"}, {\"begin\": 3264, \"end\": 3267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9999996725328483, \"rank\": 3.207416199099e-07, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}, {\"begin\": 3303, \"end\": 3308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9999260910169231, \"rank\": 3.5833116638571516e-05, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fatigue from having to chase back on combined with leading the group likely set in for the Brit.\", \"from\": 3441, \"to\": 3537, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But, after a game of cat and mouse on the final lap, and the two leaders switching roles, it was the final woods section that would prove decisive for the victory - and unpopular from the French home crowd.\", \"from\": 3538, \"to\": 3744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3726, \"end\": 3732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5283335288426827, \"rank\": 0.571347178430999, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two riders took separate lines around a tree, and almost came together.\", \"from\": 3745, \"to\": 3820, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock was marginally ahead as they rejoined the main track, and Koretzky was forced to brake and unclip from his pedal.\", \"from\": 3821, \"to\": 3942, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ELANCOURT, FRANCE - JULY 29: A general view of Charlie Aldridge of Team Great Britain competes while fans cheers during the Men's Cross-Country on day three of the Olympic Games Paris 2024 at Elancourt Hill on July 29, 2024 in Elancourt, France.\", \"from\": 3944, \"to\": 4189, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3944, \"end\": 3953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"score\": 0.9725613440037943, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ELANCOURT\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\"}, {\"begin\": 3999, \"end\": 4007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\", \"score\": 0.9999983764441359, \"rank\": 9.69580076927817e-07, \"text\": \"Aldridge\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\"}, {\"begin\": 4171, \"end\": 4180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"score\": 0.9725613440037943, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elancourt\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\"}, {\"begin\": 4182, \"end\": 4188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9927673758718502, \"rank\": 0.004530458483080368, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Photo by Tim de Waele/Getty Images)  Unfortunately for Koretsky, the loss of momentum proved too much and Pidcock accelerated away, sprinting ahead to his second gold medal at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 4190, \"to\": 4380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4213, \"end\": 4218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9999260910169231, \"rank\": 3.5833116638571516e-05, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French crowd were less than emphatic with Pidcock's victory, and we will not be surprised if French newspapers call for his head after denying the French XCO double.\", \"from\": 4381, \"to\": 4550, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4385, \"end\": 4391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5283335288426827, \"rank\": 0.571347178430999, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4478, \"end\": 4484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5283335288426827, \"rank\": 0.571347178430999, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4532, \"end\": 4538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5283335288426827, \"rank\": 0.571347178430999, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But hey, at leastPinarello/Ineos Grenadiers got two wins, right?\", \"from\": 4551, \"to\": 4615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4578, \"end\": 4594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ineos Grenadiers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a post-race interview to Adam Blythe of Discovery Plus/Eurosport, Tom Pidcock was unapologetic about his last lap move; \\\"Rubbing's racing!\\\"\", \"from\": 4617, \"to\": 4759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4645, \"end\": 4656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Blythe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Blythe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Blythe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Blythe\"}, {\"begin\": 4686, \"end\": 4697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"the young star said, quotingDays of Thunder(the NASCAR film with Tom Cruise).\", \"from\": 4760, \"to\": 4837, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4808, \"end\": 4814, \"title\": \"